      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>A molecular model of aspirin (acetylsalicylic acid) is shown. Identify the hybridization of the orbitals on each carbon atom in aspirin, and tell which atoms have lone pairs of electrons (black = C, red = O, gray = H).</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBb3NVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--7723a659b376749792cc1989a52a617a3af69b00/OChem_01_08_004.jpg\" alt=\"The ball and stick model of aspirin, also called acetylsalicylic acid where grey, black, and red spheres represent hydrogen, carbon, and oxygen, respectively.\">",
      "answers": [],
      "hints": [],
      "formats": [
        "free-response"
      ],
      "combo_choices": [],
      "collaborator_solutions": [
        {
          "images": [],
          "solution_type": "detailed",
          "content_html": "<p>All carbons except CH<sub>3</sub> are <i>sp</i><sup>2</sup>.</p>\n<img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBb3dVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--1f9be8a5840d63db2251b43578295d659830d444/OChem_01_EC_208.jpg\" alt=\"The chemical structure of aspirin featuring two lone pairs on each oxygen atom.\">"
